In the field of [[computer graphics]], '''Sequential Euclidean Distance Transforms (SEDT)''' are a special kind of [[distance transform]]s based on the [[Euclidean distance|Euclidean]] [[Metric (mathematics)|metric]] which use [[multi-valued]] [[coordinate vector|vector]] elements to propagate distances.

